                            <comment id="14079" author="laisiyao" created="Tue, 10 May 2011 02:01:44 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;static int parse_buffer(int fdin, int fdout)
{
        ...
        readhdr:
                rc = read(fdin, ptr, count);
                if (rc &amp;lt;= 0)
                         goto print;
        ...
                if (hdr-&amp;gt;ph_len &amp;gt; 4094 ||       /* is this header bogus? */
                    hdr-&amp;gt;ph_cpu_id &amp;gt; 65536 ||
                    hdr-&amp;gt;ph_stack &amp;gt; 65536 ||
                    hdr-&amp;gt;ph_sec &amp;lt; (1 &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 30) ||
                    hdr-&amp;gt;ph_usec &amp;gt; 1000000000 ||
                    hdr-&amp;gt;ph_line_num &amp;gt; 65536) {
                        ...
                        if (HDR_SIZE - count &amp;gt; 0) {
                                int left = HDR_SIZE - count;

                                memmove(buf, buf + count, left);
                                ptr = buf + left;

                                goto readhdr;
                        }
        ...
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  

&lt;p&gt;return value of retried readhdr may be 0 for the case described above, and this malformed line is silently ignored.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14078" author="laisiyao" created="Tue, 10 May 2011 01:35:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a bit interesting: when the length of malformed line is less than sizeof(struct ptldebug_header), it&apos;s not counted into bad lines if this line is at the end of the log file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will fix the test script to reflect this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
